&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Payroll Officer – Band 5 (Fixed Term – 12 Months for Maternity cover)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Senior Payroll Officer to join our Payroll Team here at Wye Valley NHS Trust. We are looking for an enthusiastic individual with knowledge in Payroll systems and PAYE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to work in a busy Payroll department to update and maintain payroll records within the Wye Valley Trusts NHS ESR system (Electronic Staff Record). It is essential for applicants to have knowledge of NHS terms and conditions of employment and ideally knowledge of the ESR system&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Payroll Officer, attention to detail is paramount for this role and accuracy is constantly monitored and is vital for a quality payroll. You will be expected to co-ordinate and oversee the complete end to end processing of the monthly payrolls, including e-roster &amp; expenses administration, all working to specified timetables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interacting closely with other HR and Finance teams, you will need to have a flexible approach to your work, as well as the ability to use your own initiative whilst working efficiently as part of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact: Alison Shaw, Payroll Manager email: alison.shaw@wvt.nhs.ukor Diana Grace, Payroll Team Leader email:diana.grace@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
